Almost one-million people in Johannesburg need food aid during the lockdown. The City of Joburg is planning to use the South African Social Security Agency’s data to find out those who are not on the welfare system. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Another unsatisfactory day for many at the Sassa office in Pretoria. Some people, who waited hours to be helped, were turned back after officials said no disability grant applications or inquiries would be attended to. Sassa spokesperson Paseka Letsatsi said these beneficiaries have been included in the COVID-19 social grants. READ: Sassa blames backlog for long queues at some offices Sassa says it's working at one-third of its capacity as per lockdown regulations. Just over a million people have applied for the R350 monthly COVID-19 relief grant. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.